Git is distributed version control system.
git is developed by linus torvalds same guy developed linux.
vcs:------------>basically it record the changes the files.(it is software)
Git having the ability of revert the change .
Git only not record the source code, it also tracks text , image , all types of files.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Three types of vcs( local, central ,distributed)

local:copy files to another directory in local(backup in another directory or hardDrive and renaming as date and time of folder)

centralized:collaborate to other developer on single file. Single server system and having all files 
and everyone is taking files from center.Admini have full access.


distributed:Server depencency less , because if server not working , we can make commit on local and when server start we push.

